                <note rend="inline" type="source">368.117/116: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-28T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1921—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Your despatch 761 August 23,<note n="32" xml:id="d167fn32">Not
                        printed.</note> and telegram 126 August 24.</p>
                <p>Inform Greek government this government anxiously awaiting compliance with
                    requests made Department’s telegram No. 54.<note n="33" xml:id="d167fn33">Dated
                        June 18, <ref target="#pg_172">p. 172</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Nicholas Kouris, passport 148581 March 3, 1921, telegraphs from Athens asking
                    release from Greek army. States he served in American army. Request immediate
                    release.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
